         <abstract id="aspace_c473f403f0743fb4fbbce65e89abd97b">The records document the first decade of Aurora's existence. The collection contains tax receipts for local businesses and citizens, trader's licenses, abstracts of mine titles, stock documents, and papers of the Independent Order of Odd Fellows, Esmeralda Lodge No. 6. A few records relate to the Kimbal  Canfield company's business in El Dorado County.</abstract>
